Scope note (what the MIT grant above covers, and the rest):

- SOURCE CODE — the MIT license above. © Peter Baer. Reuse freely with
  attribution.

- TRAINED MODEL WEIGHTS (the browser Model Capsule under viz/public/weights/,
  and the larger models under model/) — dedicated to the PUBLIC DOMAIN under
  CC0 1.0 Universal (https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/),
  matching their training data. You may use, copy, modify, and distribute them
  for any purpose, including commercially, with no conditions. (Only the small
  browser model is committed here; the large models are gitignored for size.)

- TRAINING DATA — entirely openly-licensed human games from Lichess (the Lichess
  Elite database and the Lichess standard monthly database), which Lichess
  dedicates to the public domain under CC0. The corpus and shards under data/
  are gitignored only for size; they carry no licensing encumbrance.

- THIRD-PARTY components keep their own licenses (not covered by the grants
  above):
    * Stockfish (bin/stockfish-*.exe) — GPLv3, © the Stockfish developers. Used
      only as a separate program for strength evaluation; not linked into this
      code and not used in training. Source: https://github.com/official-stockfish/Stockfish
    * pgn-extract (bin/pgn-extract.exe) — GPL, © David J. Barnes.
      https://www.cs.kent.ac.uk/people/staff/djb/pgn-extract/
    * cburnett chess pieces (web tool) — BSD, © Colin M.L. Burnett. Full terms
      and attribution in viz/THIRD_PARTY.md.

See the README "Provenance and license" section.
